using a closed-ended questionnaire. The communities were divided into
two groups with low (LC) and high (HC) level of dependence on income
from milk and animal sales. The survey results showed that cattle
production on the LC farms was based on less land and a smaller herd
(3.32 ha/farm, 1.06 lactating cows) than on HC farms (10.28 ha/farm,
