sitivity compared to the POC-CCA and qPCR despite it being the most commonly preferred method of choice to diagnose S. mansoni infections. qPCR showed superior sensitivity followed by POC-CCA, hence it can be used as an alternative or to confirm the results obtained by the Kato-Katz technique.
