n the lodging rate. The plant height, length of the basal third internode and centre of gravity height revealed remarkable positive corrlations with the lodging rate; in addition, the stalk bending resistance strength of the basal third internode revealed remarkable negative corrlation with the lodging rate over the two years. These relationships suggest that increasing stalk strength and decreasing centre of gravity height and plant height result in higher lodging resistance and should be considered in future maize breeding programmes.
